I have completed the M9 UI/UX polish task. Here is a summary of the accomplishments and the verification status:

### 1. Work Accomplished
- **Responsive Layout & Visual Balance**:
  - Restructured the incident room details page (`/incidents/[id]`) into a clean, staged sequential flow that visually reflects the progression of the incident response lifecycle.
  - Placed the **Chronological Timeline** and **Telemetry Evidence** cards side-by-side inside a responsive `.grid-12` wrapper (taking `col-span-4` and `col-span-8` respectively) at the bottom, which fully eliminates the severe height-imbalance from the original layout.
- **Aesthetic Refinement (GitLab Pajamas & Atlassian Elegance)**:
  - Swapped out the generic navy/purple/neon style in `global.css` for a professional, flat, dark slate/graphite theme.
  - Restructured status colors to use neutral, clear tones: cool blue/teal (`#0ea5e9`) brand accent, warm amber (`#f59e0b`) warnings, and verified green (`#10b981`).
  - Solved dark-theme WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility contrast violations by introducing a high-contrast light red (`#f87171`) for error text/badges/redaction labels on dark surfaces, and a robust solid red (`#dc2626`) background for `btn-danger` buttons. Changed primary button text to `--bg-main` to pass contrast checks against `#0ea5e9`.
  - Removed decorative box-shadow glows and text gradients in favor of predictable, clean borders.
- **Overflow & Containment**:
  - Handled long SHA-256 hashes, PR URLs, and raw provenance telemetry blocks inside card boundaries on both desktop and mobile viewports by applying `word-break: break-all` and `overflow-wrap: anywhere`.
- **E2E Automation**:
  - Created a dedicated E2E test file [m9-ui-refinement.spec.ts](file:///C:/Users/Atchayam/AppData/Local/Temp/incident-m9-ui-refinement/apps/web/e2e/m9-ui-refinement.spec.ts) asserting the absence of horizontal overflow, correct visual ordering, hash wrapping, and programmatic capture of the four submission screenshots.
- **Submission Screenshots**:
  - Automatically regenerated and saved all four submission screenshots in [docs/submission/screenshots/](file:///C:/Users/Atchayam/AppData/Local/Temp/incident-m9-ui-refinement/docs/submission/screenshots/) using the real local SQLite API state under desktop viewports (`1440x1000`).
- **Handoff & Verification Documentation**:
  - Created [m9-ui-refinement.md](file:///C:/Users/Atchayam/AppData/Local/Temp/incident-m9-ui-refinement/docs/testing/m9-ui-refinement.md) (testing/QA report) and [M9_UI_REFINEMENT_AGY_HANDOFF.md](file:///C:/Users/Atchayam/AppData/Local/Temp/incident-m9-ui-refinement/docs/project/agent-runs/M9_UI_REFINEMENT_AGY_HANDOFF.md) (agent run handoff summary).

